        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T17:55:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i am worried that this has the same problem as grpcutil.Tag, which has place only for the status, but cannot contain status details. As a result, status and status details might be coming from different channels and therefore not guaranteed to correspond to each other. This is what inspired me to create appstatus package, see this description: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/1984537/11//COMMIT_MSG#10\n\nin buildbucket context this means that status and status details are coming from different channels.\nAs a user of this package, I am unable to tag a error with INFRA_FAILURE and details that aren\u0027t expressible via specific errors\n\nso i wonder if the tag value should be a struct with both status and status details:\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/grpc/appstatus/status.go;l\u003d57?q\u003dappstatus",
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4a7b560d_7182a17d",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/build/errors.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:22:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good call; I\u0027ll rework this to be in the style of appstatus (I hadn\u0027t seen it before)\n\nI think precluding overrides will also be fine, since I don\u0027t plan to implement \"infra_step\" style magic here; Running a subprocess will return a normal error (default FAILURE) and users will be able to add an explicit INFRA_ERROR status via this mechanism if they want to upgrade it.",
