      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T17:55:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why is this responsibility of Sink.Use() as opposed to the caller? (SRP)\n\ni suspect the reason is that Use() is called from mkRawRun and mkRun. It makes sense for them, but given that this is a public func, I am not sure it makes sense for anyone else. Should we create a new private func that does this and calls Use(), and use that private func in mkRawRun/mkRun?",
