    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6d89f67e_7a813af1",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/build/sink.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 149,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:22:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason I have it here is so that `lastBuild` has consistent behavior for all uses of Sink. The reason why \u0027build\u0027 is a separate package from `exe` is because I anticipate that folks will need/want to use Sink pretty often (at the very least from tests).\n\nI agree that it\u0027s awkward that mkRawRun implements this again... however I suspect that mkRawRun will be used by exactly one thing (run_subannotations). I\u0027d rather have mkRawRun be the relatively grungy path while Sink is trivially correct to use.",
      "parentUuid": "929c3468_155bf4d7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 138,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 149,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
