      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T17:55:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "we hold two locks at the same time here. I think this increases the risk of deadlocks, but it is totally unavoidable. Also not sure we want to signal new ver if cb failed?\n\nwhy not\n\n  s.modMu.RLock()\n  if s.detached {\n    s.modMu.RUnlock()\n    return ErrBuildDetached\n  }\n  err :\u003d cb()\n  s.modMu.RUnlock()\n\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n     s.signalNewVersionLocked()\n  }",
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "282121b2_50a99238",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/build/state.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:22:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We shouldn\u0027t ever deadlock because we always respect the lock order; I\u0027ll add some heavier documentation around modMu.\n\nI think we should signal regardless; Note that all uses of modLock apply edits to the build even when cb returns an error.\n\nIf we wanted to fancy we\u0027d only signal \"if there was a change\", but this is more complex to compute and imo not worth it.",
      "parentUuid": "a1dd6564_cf7cf91b",
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
