    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0062fd46_b41b3c4d",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/exe.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 160,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:22:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, this is documented (though maybe in a subsequent CL). It\u0027s needed because otherwise users could launch subprocesses with, at the very least, invalid LOGDOG_NAMESPACE (and later LUCI_CONTEXT) values.\n\nIn recipes which exist, they _frequently_ manipulate the environment so that \"further down the stack\" operates with a modified environment. Without clearing the environment programs will have subtle bugs where some sections will operate on `os.Environ` (as global state) and others will correctly use the context-embedded environment. By clearing the os environment we can preclude most of those subtle bugs because environment variables won\u0027t be accessible via os.Environ at all, which should serve as a clue that this it is the wrong channel.",
      "parentUuid": "987eeaf0_302638d5",
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
