    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f219a6e2_38d66517",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/options.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:07:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My feeling is that the vast majority of uses will not need to supply anything in the context which is consumed by Run; If they need to install additional things, they\u0027ll do it inside of their main function. This option is provided as an escape hatch in case the user really wants to mock clock, logging or something else.",
      "parentUuid": "330205d0_4d8a047f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a156049_7eed6dbe",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/options.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T18:10:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think so too, but I think those who need to pass a context, might not be happy with this. What\u0027s the problem in accept context?\n\nstepping back, my general concern that applies to a couple of other comments, is that this code might be trying to solve more problems that it designed to solve, i.e. scope creep, i.e. something that happened to recipes before. \n\nwould it be possible to scope all of this only to production of Build proto? this really the only problem this code should help solving.",
      "parentUuid": "f219a6e2_38d66517",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e703630c_9eb63e4c",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/options.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002639
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T20:29:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I do agree that I\u0027d be happier with a leaner interface.\n\nAs an example, I implemented the Build update for cros_test_platform.execute in https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/infra/cmd/cros_test_platform/internal/execution/build/build.go\n\nGranted, that implementation \n[1] doesn\u0027t have concurrency at all\n[2] doesn\u0027t create any logdog streams.\n\nNow, I do want to add [2], but possibly don\u0027t ever want [1].\n\nIn that situation, I\u0027d be happier with a leaner library that lets me do [2] without a lot of extra cost (in terms of complexity of the interface primarily, but also the complexity of the implementation to some extent, \u0027cause all abstractions are leaky).\n\ne.g., I\u0027m unlikely to care about:\n- concurrency\n  - corollary: fine grained locking -- if I do add concurrency, it\u0027s like to be such that simply locking the whole Build message and updating a bunch of steps at once is adequate. Simpler concurrency implementation is likely to be easier to reason about / less likely to be buggy.\n- any kind of property namespaces\n\n--\n\nNow, I\u0027m in favor of _some_ higher abstraction library than currently exists. So whatever shape this library lands in, I\u0027d be interested in moving to that for my implementation. But I\u0027d be happier with something a bit more like a library and bit less like a framework :)",
      "parentUuid": "6a156049_7eed6dbe",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "61b30da391e48266c42f8b59416d22727e7de471",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e8607acd_f5985a47",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/options.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-24T21:02:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e more like a library and bit less like a framework :)\n\n+1 to this. This is actually what I wrote in a draft, but didn\u0027t send out.\n\n\u003e unlikely to care about concurrency\n\ndoes this mean that it is better to decouple build-sending from concurrency-build-mutations? e.g. the sending part could assume that all mutations are synchronized, and a separate helper struct could implement smart synchronization\n\nthis is an example of my general concern that orthogonal things get coupled unnecessarily",
      "parentUuid": "e703630c_9eb63e4c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 102,
